  "original_title": "\u0db1\u0dd0\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0d91\u0db1 \u0dc3\u0d82\u0da0\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0d9a\u0dba\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca\u0da7 \u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dcf\u0dba\u0dda \u0db4\u0dc4\u0dc3\u0dd4\u0d9a\u0db8\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0da9\u0dd2 \u0d9a\u0dd9\u0dbb\u0dda",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The facilities of the port will be increased for tourists coming by ship",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Mr. Nimal Siripala de Silva, the Minister of Ports, Shipping and Aviation Services, said that for the foreign tourists coming to Sri Lanka by ships, the Colombo Port will be improved with modern facilities at the passenger terminal facilities.",
        "The minister said this when he came to inspect the current condition of the passenger terminal premises at Colombo Port.",
        "Further stating the facts, the minister said, 'According to the information obtained in the past years, tourist passenger ships have arrived at the port of Colombo in large numbers. But due to the covid epidemic situation and the economic instability in the country in recent days, the arrival of these passenger ships has stopped. But aiming at the upcoming tourist season, the passenger terminal and the premises should be equipped with modern facilities in such a way as to attract tourists.'",
        "Minister Nimal Siripala de Silva said that arrangements should be made to provide an air-conditioned parking hall with modern facilities, sanitary facilities, an attractive duty-free shopping mall, and transportation facilities.",
        "The Minister said that he had discussed with all shipping companies and representatives of Sri Lanka in order to bring these passenger ships to Sri Lanka and said that the business promotion division of the port should implement a large publicity program on the Internet.",
        "The minister also said that he is dedicated to contribute to the port's contribution to the foreign exchange program initiated by the government.",
        "A group of officials, including Mr. KDS Ruwanchandra, Secretary of the Ministry of Ports, Shipping and Aviation, Mr. Gayan Algewattage, Vice President of the Sri Lanka Ports Authority, also participated in this inspection tour."
      ],
